@startuml lsl-repo-split
!include _standard-style.puml

title Public repo + private LSL companion: how they split

skinparam folder {
  BackgroundColor<<workspace>> #FAFAFA
  BorderColor #888888
  FontStyle bold
}

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<public>> #E8F5E8
  BackgroundColor<<private>> #FFF2E6
  BackgroundColor<<gitignore>> #FFFACD
}

skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor<<public_host>> #E8F5E8
  BackgroundColor<<private_host>> #FFF2E6
  BorderColor #555555
}

actor Developer as dev

folder "Local working tree\n~/Agentic/<project>/" as ws <<workspace>> {
  component "Source code\n(src/, docs/, tests/, ...)\n" as src <<public>>
  component ".gitignore\nblocks .specstory/history/" as ign <<gitignore>>
  component ".specstory/history/\n(nested git repo)\n  <yyyy>/<mm>/*.md\n  logs/" as hist <<private>>
}

cloud "Public host (github.com)\n<user>/<project>" as pub <<public_host>> {
  component "Source code +\nproject docs" as pub_code <<public>>
}

cloud "Private LSL host (bmw.ghe.com)\n<org>/<project>-history" as priv <<private_host>> {
  component "<yyyy>/<mm>/*.md  (transcripts)\nlogs/  (LSL routing logs)" as priv_logs <<private>>
}

dev --> ws : edits / runs `coding`

src -[#2E7D32]-> pub_code : git push (public)
hist -[#E65100]-> priv_logs : git push (private)
ign .[#B8860B].> hist : excludes from\nouter repo

note bottom of ws
  Two git repos in one working tree:
  - the **outer** repo tracks code; .specstory/history/ is .gitignore'd
  - the **inner** repo at .specstory/history/ tracks LSL transcripts only,
    pushing to the private companion — never to the public host
end note

@enduml
